37 services; the secretary of the executive office of labor and workforce development; a
38 representative from the Massachusetts Association of Early Education and Care; a representative
39 of Strategies for Children; a representative from Neighborhood Villages; a representative from
40 United Way of Massachusetts Bay and Merrimack Valley; a representative from Massachusetts
41 Early Education Funders Collaborative; Massachusetts Business Roundtable; a representative
42 from the Rennie Center for Education Research and Policy; a representative from the
43 Massachusetts Budget and Policy Center; a representative from the Massachusetts Taxpayer’s
44 Foundation; a representative from the Massachusetts Association of School Superintendents who
45 must also be from a current CPPI community; a representative from an advanced CPPI
46 community; a representative from the Massachusetts Head Start Association; a representative
47 from SEIU 509, which represents family child care providers; a representative from an
48 independent family child care program; a representative from the Massachusetts Resource and
49 Referral Network; a representative from the Massachusetts Municipal Association; a
50 representative from Care that Works; a representative of the Massachusetts Afterschool
51 Partnership, a representative from the Massachusetts Alliance of YMCAs; a representative of the
52 Massachusetts Alliance of Boys and Girls Clubs; a representative from Massachusetts
53 Association for Community Action; and no more than 5 additional members to be appointed by
54 the co-chairs, at least one of whom shall represent parents and families.
55 Commissioners shall use principles of economic and social justice to guide their work
56 and shall collaborate with existing working groups and task forces. The commission shall create
57 findings and recommendations based on their study and should consider and recommend ways
58 that resources can be utilized most efficiently, effectively, and equitably.
59 All appointments should be made no later than 60 days after the effective date of this act.
